window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>As the days grow shorter and the temperature drops, Halloween approaches. Come, brave listener, pull up a chair, and spend some time with master storyteller Stephen Fry as he tells us some of his favourite ghost stories of all time, in truly terrifying spatial audio.</p> <p>From the headless horseman of Sleepy Hollow to the tortured spirits of M.R. James, from Edgar Allan Poe’s terrifying tale of a doppelganger to Charlotte Riddell’s Open Door that should definitely stay shut, join Stephen as he tells you some truly terrifying tales of ghosts and ghouls, spirits and phantasms, spectres and apparitions. Listener discretion advised.</p> <p>This collection includes:</p> <p><i>The Legend of Sleepy Hollow</i> by Washington Irving</p> <p><i>Lonely Hearts</i> by M.R. James</p> <p><i>Was It an Illusion?</i> by Amelia B. Edwards</p> <p><i>The Body Snatcher</i> by Robert Louis Stevenson</p> <p><i>The Empty House</i> by Algernon Blackwood</p> <p><i>William Wilson</i> by Edgar Alan Poe</p> <p><i>The Open Door</i> by Charlotte Riddell</p> <p><i>The Judge's House</i> by Bram Stoker</p> <p>Now available in Dolby Atmos on Audible.</p>"; 
